Abakaliki – As the increasing rate of gunmen attacks continue to ravage the South East, some yet to be identified gunmen have shot dead one Nnaemeka Chukwu, nine days to his wedding in Abakaliki, Ebonyi State capital city. The deceased who was popularly known as Ochoudo, deals on provisions within the Abakaliki city and has two shops. He was killed in front of his shop after closing Monday night. He hailed from Enyibichiri Alike community, in the Ikwo Local Government Area of Ebonyi State. The deceased who had concluded arrangement for his wedding billed for April 21, 2022, was with his fiancée identified as Favour Chioma, when he was gunned down by the assassins. A relative who spoke to our reporter said: “He has a shop at the International Market where he deals in provision goods. He owns another joint at Chukwuma Ofeke Street Ameke Aba. “The incident according to the wife happened at about 9pm when they had closed shop and were about to enter their vehicle. “Some boys accosted them, first shot into the air, then ordered the guy to lie down and then shot him three times, collected the wife’s phone and left.” The pre-wedding pictures with the couple-to-be had gone viral on social media following his death. His wedding invitation obtained by our Reporter revealed that the traditional marriage was to take place on April 21 at his Fiancée’s Father’s compound in Amaiyima Ekpelu, in Ikwo local government. POLL The wedding was slated to be held on April 23 at Pastoral Centre, Mile 50 Abakaliki with reception at International Conference Centre, Abakaliki, the state capital. The Police Public Relations Officer, in the state, DSP Loveth Odah said she was not aware of the incident. She, however, promised to get back to our correspondent after contacting the officer in-charge of the area. She was yet to do so as of the time of filing this report